UPI fraud is a common type of cybercrime where attackers trick users into making unauthorized payments. A typical scenario involves a scammer pretending to be a bank official or customer support executive. The scammer contacts the victim through a phone call or message and claims there is an issue with their bank account or offers a reward or cashback.

The victim is then asked to click on a link or approve a payment request on their UPI app. Many users mistakenly believe they are receiving money, but in reality, they are authorizing a payment. Once the request is approved, money is deducted instantly from the victim’s account.

Students, elderly people, and individuals unfamiliar with digital payment systems are often targeted. The consequences include financial loss, stress, and loss of trust in online platforms.

This case highlights the importance of awareness while using digital payment systems and the need to verify any suspicious requests before taking action.
